DURBAN Lions centre Lionel Mapoe has replaced Jesse Kriel in the Springbok midfield for Saturday s second Test against France in Durban.Kriel was ruled out of second Test contention with concussion.READ: Coetzee: A step in the right directionSpringbok coach Allister Coetzee said that for the sake of continuity the selection this week wasn t difficult. The team did so well last week, there was no need to make changes. However, we were forced to bring in a No 13 and Lionel Mapoe fits the bill there. I think he (Mapoe) is very much an underrated player, said Coetzee.Boks starting 15: 15 Andries Coetzee, 14 Raymond Rhule, 13 Lionel Mapoe, 12 Jan Serfontein, 11 Courtnall Skosan, 10 Elton Jantjies, 9 Ross Cronje, 8 Warren Whiteley (captain), 7 Oupa Mohoje, 6 Siya Kolisi, 5 Franco Mostert, 4 Eben Etzebeth, 3 Frans Malherbe, 2 Malcolm Marx, 1 Tendai Mtawarira.Substitutes: 16 Bongi Mbonambi, 17 Steven Kitshoff, 18 Coenie Oosthuizen, 19 Pieter-Steph du Toit, 20 Jean-Luc du Preez, 21 Francois Hougaard, 22 Frans Steyn, 23 Dillyn Leyds. The #Springbok team to face France in Durban on Saturday. #LoveRugby #BokCountry @MTNza @ASICS_ZA pic.twitter.com/BKvzZvpr4F African News Agency